The Five Love Languages

My primary love language is probably
Physical Touch
with a secondary love language being
Words of Affirmation.

Complete set of results

Physical Touch: 11
Words of Affirmation: 8
Receiving Gifts: 5
Quality Time: 4
Acts of Service: 2


Information

Unhappiness in relationships, according to Dr. Gary Chapman, is often due to the fact that we speak different love languages. Sometimes we don't understand our partner's requirements, or even our own. We all have a ""love tank"" that needs to be filled in order for us to express love to others, but there are different means by which our tank can be filled, and there are different ways that we can express love to others.

column1: event,"Hey cool... people still read my LJ! hehe

I'm still just going to nursing school.  I have T-1 year left.  Next semester is peds/maternity, which is exciting.  I'm not working, so I've basically just spent this break being as much of a pile of crap as I can.

I don't normally do resolutions, but this year I need to seriously lose some poundage.  I'm in Amber's wedding in July, and I refuse to be the extremely fat bridesmaid.  So, I'm going to do the workout thing again (at a gym closer to my house this time so it doesn't take a 2 hour block of time to drive there, workout, drive home, and shower) and make my own meals (because my mom cooks shit, basically. good shit, but shit none the less).  I think all of this came about because I realized I weigh the most I've weighed since highschool, which is simply not cool with me.  It's not really a resolution, more of a goal.

Anyway, it's new years eve and I have no plans... and I kind of like it that way.  It's not that exciting to me... it just means I have to remember to write 06 on things.  Oh, and I can actually say ""I graduate this year"" in 2006.
The love life blows, but that's pretty normal. We'll just not talk about that. lol

Accutane update (yes I'm still on it)  Month 5 I do believe.  My skin isn't dry, but isn't oily, and I don't break out.  I have some clogged pore spots, but they're not inflamed so they don't actually turn into zits.  Yeah. That's about it.  It's going well, except my triglycerides shot up.  But they'll go back down when I go off it in a month, so it's not that big of a deal.  My liver and everything else is ok, so it's not a concern.
Anyway, have a happy new year and I'll talk to ya'll in 06!"

event,"What does it mean to be a WSU Cougar?
It means you're part of a shared experience, a common bond gained by living in a unique town in a unique place.
It means you know to watch for the dark blue car in Colfax and keep your speed under 30 mph.
It means you know the taste of the fry sauce at Cougar Country.
It means you know the difference between Dismores and Safeway and The Cougar Cafe and The Coug.
It means you know every turn in the road from Pullman to Moscow, day or night, and in rain, snow or sunshine.
It means you know at least one other person who you spent so much time with that you can call them any time, any day, and have a listening ear.
It means that anywhere you go in the world, if you wear a WSU hat, you're ready to hear ""Go Cougs"" from a total stranger.

It means that people from big metropolitan schools don't understand what we know - what it's like to center your life on a small town for a few years, and to see those as a shared, wonderful experience.
It means you root for the little guy. It means you understand Rodney Dangerfield when he says ""I don't get no respect.""
It means you were surprised this fall when WSU was referred to on ESPN.
It means you know what it's like to win another Apple Cup - and to be ready to come back next year and go after them again.
It means you had the unaccustomed sensation of expecting to actually WIN games this year.
It means you know that victory can be snatched from the jaws of defeat and vice versa - and that both will happen in the same football season.
It means that whether the Cougs win or lose, you know it will NOT last...and that you'll be back for more.
It means you feel comfortable walking past Bryan hall, and you occasionally smile when you look up at the red clock face.
It means you know how valuable a 30-gallon trash bag is when you sit in Martin Stadium on a windy day.
It means you know the layout of the CUB, and where The Coug is.
It means you know ""The Bookie"" is a store, not a person.
It means that when winter rolls around it's ok to a laugh when people fall walking up the icy hills to class as long as you know your turn is coming soon.
It means that when you're in a car driving through the rolling Palouse hills in the spring and see spring wheat rippling in the wind, you find it soothing and beautiful.
It means you know which cliff is ""The Cliff"".
It means you know which Pullman streets NEVER to drive on when it's icy in winter.
It means that whenever you meet another Cougar, you feel a little bit of a special bond, even if you're very different people"

event,"Well, the Accutane is working.  My skin is all dry, but still managable dry.  I'm not breaking out perse, but I have clogged pores. Not zits, but clogged pores.  It's weird.  Oh well, it's a lot better than it was before, so I'll take it.

I go back for my one month check up tomorrow.  I'm going to try to convince him to let me pee on a stick instead of having blood prego tests because they're expensive.  I talked to his nurse and she told me to hold off on my blood work till I talked to him. So yeah.  *swoons* hot dermatologst man!
event,"My face is dry and peeling. My skin is itchy and flakey. My lips require constant attention.  My scalp is dry and flakey, which is probably the worst part.  Grar.  The things i go through...."

event,"Face: drying.  Spots still produce oil, but very very little of it.  I am have a breakout thing going on right now, but it gets worse before it gets better, so I'll deal.  I was my face twice a day with Dove facewash and put moisturizer on.

Hair: DRY AS ALL HELL.  Well, my scalp is dry, which translates into dry hair. Have no fear.  I bought Catwalk Oatmeal and Honey shampoo and conditioner.  Not only smells edible, but works quite nicely.
Lips: ""Aquaphor is my friend"" says my lips."

event,"Holy shit!  Ok so when I woke up this morning my skin was ok.  It wasn't overly dry and it wasn't really oily.  I went to work out, came home and showered.  When I got out of the shower I went to put on some makeup... MY SKIN IS PEELING LIKE A MOFO!  It's insane.  I just put an entire sample of Clinique Moisture Surge Extra Thirsty Skin Relief on my skin and it feels like it needs more.  I know this is normal and it's what I was expecting, but I wasn't expecting it to happen so soon!  I'm going to go roll in some aloe."

event,"My lips are dry. My arms are dry. My back is dry.  My face is less oily than normal.  The accutane is giving me a headache, so right now I take more pills to counteract the side effects than I do of the actual med.  I take the vitamin E and now I take ibuprofen. Sweet. I bought foundation I can wear when my skin dries out too. woo.

In other news: I got my info about clinicals next semester.  And a list of school supplies, which just stressed me out because I don't have money for it and I haven't heard from Job Lady yet. Oh, and the accutane labs are going to be over $100 a month.  It'll be less if I can get the prego test taken off there (it's like $42. can't i just be on an effing stick and be done with it?). Ugh."

event,"Well, from here on out this is basically going to be my Accutane update journal.  I started it today.  I take 80mg a day, and 800 IU of Vitamin E to help lessen the Accutane symptoms.  Hopefully this crap works!!  I'm armed with a lot of moisturizers, including some Oil of Olay for extra dry skin (body wash AND moisturizer for face), Aquaphor Healing Ointment, and Eucerin Dry Skin Therapy for my body lotion (since I can't very well slather myself in Aquaphor ointment) and various other Clinique free samples.  If any of you see me in public, I'll probably be sucking on a bottle of water and peeling off my skin. And I might have to invest in moisturizing shampoo and conditioner, but we'll see how bad my hair/scalp get before i do that.  For now, your pimpley friend...
PS: I might post before and afters of this process, if ya'll are nice and don't make fun of my zits."

event,"So I took a percocet at midnight, then proceeded to lay in bed and think about my interview next week and how I could correctly answer questions to get that job.  I'm so cool.  Then I got hot, so i took off my shirt and found a tank top. so here I sit, in a tank top and underwear, contemplating the meaning off life while being a ltitle doped up.  But the good news is... now my jaw is not tender like it was earlier.  They weren't lying when they said the lower right would be the most sensitive.  It was the one that was partially involved with the bone... yeah yeah it's tender all right.  Anyway, I'm going to go lay in bed and contemplate some more. ABout nothing.  Ah yes, to be high and smart all at once."
event,"I'm bored out of my mind."

event,"I can't sleep.  I took a percaset (sp?) at midnight and it made me super dizzy and tired... so i went to bed.  Now I'm wide awake, not dizzy, and high.  Just bored.  So I ate some apple sauce, drank some milk, took some ibuprofen, and iced my face in hopes it won't swell much in the next few days.  They told me day 3 is usually when swelling peaks.  I wish I could drive.  I have some things i want to do tomorrow, but taking percaset to keep the pain down is more important right now.  I waited 8 hours between doses last time and I started having jaw pain.  Moral of the story: if you take a pain pill when you
column2: re not in pain, but anticipate being in pain later, don't take the fact that you don't have pain as a good sign."

column1: event,"I feel pretty good, oddly enough.  I don't feel like I had 4 wisdom teeth ripped from my mouth today.  The funny thing is, I don't remember waking up, getting in the wheel chair, and being taken to a room to let more anesthesia wear off.  The last thing I remember before I fell asleep was ""This may or may not take a little bi...""  He didn't even get ""bit"" out and I was out cold.  Like 10 seconds after he got the IV in (which felt fine, btw) I started feeling floaty, then I was out.  No counting needed.  I do remember when I woke up going ""I'm done?""  ""yep. all done.  ""really?""  It was weird.  When I got home, the crappiest part was the gauze I had to change out all the time.  I finally said eff the gauze when there wasn't very much blood on it (probably more than they would've liked, but oh well) and ate some pudding.  2 pudding snacks and a class of milk later, I took a percaset and was down for the count.  I fell asleep icing my face and woke up 2 hours later a little floaty, light headed, and kinda high.  But that wore off after about 15 minutes and now I'm just painless and functioning like a normal person.

Anyway, moral of the story is: having your wisdom teeth out isn't that bad, depending on the person.  My sisters never had problems either.  So. Yeah. Not so bad kids, not so bad.  I just want to drink things through straws but I can't.  I'd like real food but when I tried to eat an egg i neglected to remember I shouldn't chew yet so it was back to pudding i went.  At least pudding is good, right?"
event,"I can't sleep so I'm eating, since I can't eat breakfast and I won't want to eat after my teeth come out.
My dog really likes wheat bread... is that weird?
My surgery is in less than 8 hours.

I said some things today to someone that I wish I had just kept to myself.  Oops. The good news is he's asleep and hasn't read them yet.  THe bad news is he has to wake up eventually and will read them.  Is there, like, a de-send button on MSN? Damnit. I didn't think so. Oh well.
Lindsey got a 2001 Jetta.  I want a new car.  Partially because I'm bored with mine, mostly because i fear it will croak on me soon and I'll be carless.
Ugh. I'm going to go eat more peaches and read and maybe sleep. ugh."
event,"I'm disgruntled.  My cumulative GPA is 3.49.  Yes kids, that's .01 away from the President's Honor Roll this semester. Sons of bitches.  My first semester in 3 years not being on it.

So I woke up at 12:30 today and I had 6 missed calls from Merle.  Weird? Yeah I thought so too considering I don't think he's called me in months.  He found the missing golden retriever.  He came over to deposit the dog and omg, yeah, he's hot.  I'm proud of that one.  I just wish it wasn't gone.  Oh well.
I have an interview with Memorial Hospital next Wednesday. yay!  She wanted to do it tomorrow but um... my wisdom teeth are coming out... so she gave me some time to heal.  YAY!"

event,"Well, last night was a fun night out with the girls I like from my class.  We bar hopped. =)
-Next Thursday, my wisdom teeth are coming out. YAY!

-Grades are in. I got a B in my hard class.  So for the semester I have: A, A-, B+, B, and a ""P"".  I would just like everyone to know that P was a 98.5%, but we don't get letters for clinical.  I'm content with my grades, considering I didn't glue myself to a book and study 24/7.

-So, let the summer reading BEGIN.  I should find a job... I'm going to apply at some places tomorrow and hope no one wants an interview between next thursday and probably the following Monday.  I mean, I'd be more than happy to interview with them as long as they don't discriminate against people who look like chipmunks, but I think being doped up could be a problem."

column1: event,"Ugh.  Well, I only have two finals then I'm done with my first semester of nursing school. YAY!

Here's the ugh part: one of my wisdom teeth is causing me mucho problems.  I have a consultation with the oral surgeon on Wednesday.  But when I was just looking at my teeth I saw my tonsils... they're big and spotty.  But they don't hurt.  Maybe the nerve just rotted out from too many infections.  Anyway, my mom wants me to go get antibiotics to clear up any infections that may be festering so i can have my teeth ripped out sooner, but that costs money.  I'll just wait for my consultation and if he thinks anything is weird, he'll give them to me before he'll rip on my teeth anyway.  Well, this sounds like it's going to be fun! Ripping out 4 teeth, not being able to eat, chipmunk cheeks (NO I WILL NOT POST PICS.  Ok, maybe).... oh yeah. and the PAIN.  At least they give you good drugs for that... right?"
I woke up because i was hot and thirsty.
I had to scream at some moron tonight for sitting on my car in the Fred Meyer parking lot. YOU JUST DON'T DO THAT.
THe lady at Fred Meyer smushed my bread with my soup cans then treated me like I was the bitch.  I knew I should've bought the beer...
Oh yeah. I'm 21 now, speaking of beer.
I'm going to Pullman next Wednesday after I'm done with finals.  Massages, hair appointments, OH MY!
I'm going to Tri Cities sometime this week. I have no idea why, besides the fact that I want a new bra.
I'm trying to find books to read this summer, since I miss leisure reading.  Anyone have any suggestions?  I really want to read The Da Vinci Code.  Any comments?"
